scissors and remove the gum cutting also

00:00:31.910 --> 00:00:38.410
hair. Stop it! Before doing this,
in this video we show you how to remove a

00:00:38.410 --> 00:00:39.660
bubble gum.

00:00:39.660 --> 00:00:40.910
Instructions:

00:00:40.910 --> 00:00:47.420
1. Apply peanut butter. This
is one of the most traditional solutions,

00:00:47.420 --> 00:00:52.530
but the truth is not always becomes
entirely effective. You should brush the chewing gum

00:00:52.530 --> 00:00:58.280
peanut butter or peanuts, this will
It will soften gradually to undo it.

00:00:58.280 --> 00:01:04.110
That's why we must hold all of your hair
and let free only affected the lock of hair,

00:01:04.110 --> 00:01:09.610
so as not to make a complete mess. Then
have to wash your hair with plenty

00:01:09.610 --> 00:01:14.869
water and possibly warm to finish
removing any sticky dough.

00:01:14.869 --> 00:01:21.869
2. Apply cooking oil. It is one of the
more recommended solutions. It's simple,

00:01:23.540 --> 00:01:28.659
you just have to apply a good amount of oil
on the gum stuck in your hair and leave

00:01:28.659 --> 00:01:34.909
act for about 15 minutes, perhaps
need a little more, and then you can remove

00:01:34.909 --> 00:01:37.740
Easily full gum.

00:01:37.740 --> 00:01:44.630
3. Apply alcohol. Is a similar alternative
peanut butter with the same disadvantage

00:01:44.630 --> 00:01:50.180
you could make the problem worse if
the gum gets tangled in the hair. Dip

00:01:50.180 --> 00:01:55.670
gum in a container with alcohol and let
act for a few minutes, this will dissolve

00:01:55.670 --> 00:02:00.619
the gum and then you can remove it with
plenty of hot water.

00:02:00.619 --> 00:02:06.549
4. Rub an ice cube. It is the choice
which requires more work as you will

00:02:06.549 --> 00:02:11.549
to spend time rubbing the gum with the
ice until it hardens, then you can

00:02:11.549 --> 00:02:15.380
break and have to go removing part
by.

